":"to incline, to tend"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shade, to blend"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"first (only in composed numbers)","examples":[{"text":"حَادٍ وَعِشْرُونَ","english":"twenty-first"},{"text":"حَادِيَةٌ وَعِشْرُونَ","english":"twenty-first"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of حَدَّ (ḥadda, “to be sharp”). Compare Hebrew חַד (ḥad, “sharp”), Old Armenian խադ (xad, “sword”).\n\nFrom ح د و (ḥ d w) via transposition of و ح د (w ḥ d), see وَاحِد (wāḥid)."},"ipa":["/ħaːdd/","/ħaːd.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7287","headword_ar":"حَادٌّ","root":"Hd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiydN","text_ar":"حَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  See also 1, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~ato","text_ar":"حَدَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n7400","headword_ar":"حَادٍ","root":"Hdw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Driving"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a driver"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of camels; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"urging"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exciting"},{"kind":"text","text":"them, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who urges"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excites"},{"kind":"text","text":"them,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by singing"},{"kind":"text","text":"to them: see 1]: (Mgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HudaApN","text_ar":"حُدَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN HaAdK","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ حَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~aA='N","text_ar":"حَدَّا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which latter is an intensive epithet]. (K.) ―         -b2-  It is also applied to a [wild] he-ass, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Driving before him his she-asses."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * TA.) He is said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdiY valaAvK","text_ar":"حَادِى ثَلَاثٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A driver before him of three"},{"kind":"text","text":"she-asses], (S, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdiY vamaAnK","text_ar":"حَادِى ثَمَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a driver before him of eight"},{"kind":"text","text":"she-asses]. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdiY","text_ar":"حَادِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~ajomi","text_ar":"النَّجْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The driver,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"urger, of the asterism"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~abaraAnu","text_ar":"الدَّبَرَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Hyades;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the five chief stars thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the brightest star thereof, a of Taurus"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdiY Aln~ujuwmi","text_ar":"حَادِى النُّجُومِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the driver,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"urger, of the stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mijodaHN","text_ar":"مِجْدَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHawaAdiY","text_ar":"الحَوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of the fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaAdiyapu","text_ar":"الحَادِيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hind legs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because they follow the fore legs. (K.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The latter"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hinder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the last,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hindmost, parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything. (Az, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdK","text_ar":"حَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also the act. part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadaA","text_ar":"حَدَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHd~Y","text_ar":"تحدّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and thus means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aiming at a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (AA, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAdiYa","text_ar":"حَادِىَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$ara","text_ar":"عَشَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.: see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wHd","text_ar":"وحد"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n9437","headword_ar":"حَادَ","root":"Hwd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHuwdu","text_ar":"يَحُودُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAda","text_ar":"حَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHiydu","text_ar":"يَحِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hyd","text_ar":"حيد"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%AF/","headword_ar":"حادَ","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_19","lexicon_en":"Firuzabadi, al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ (d. 1414 CE)","lexicon_ar":"القاموس المحيط للفيروزآبادي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=26138#aa806f","body_html":"<span>حادَ يَحودُ، كيَحيدُ.</span><br><span>وحاوِدٌ: أبو قبيلةٍ من حُدَّانَ.</span><br><span>وتُحاوِدُهُ الحُمَّى: تَتَعَهَّدُهُ.</span><br><span>وكهُودٍ: ع.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_19","lexicon_en":"Firuzabadi, al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ (d. 1414 CE)","lexicon_ar":"القاموس المحيط للفيروزآبادي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=26138#3fc717","body_html":"<span>حادَ عنه يَحِيدُ حَيْداً وحَيَداناً ومَحيداً وحُيوداً وحَيْدَةً وحَيْدودَةً: مالَ.</span><br><span>والحَيْدُ: ما شَخَص من نَواحِي الشيءِ،</span><br><span>وـ من الجَبَلِ: شاخِصٌ كأنه جَناحٌ، وكُلُّ ضِلَعٍ شديدةِ الاعْوجاجِ، والعُقْدَةُ في قَرْنِ الوَعِلِ، وكُلُّ نُتُوءٍ في قَرْنٍ أو جَبَلٍ، ج: حُيودٌ، حِيودٌ وأحْيادٌ وحِيَدٌ، كعِنبٍ، والمِثْلُ، والنَّظيرُ، ويكسرُ.</span><br><span>والحَيْدانُ، كسَحْبانَ: ما حَادَ من الحَصَى عن قَوائِمِ الدابَّةِ في السَّيْرِ.</span><br><span>والحَيَدُ، محركةً: الطعامُ، وأن يَنْشَبَ ولَدُ الشاةِ، ولم يَسْهُلْ مَخْرَجُهُ.</span><br><span>والحَيَدى، كجَمزى: مِشْيَةُ المُخْتالِ.</span><br><span>وحِمارٌ حَيَدَى وحَيِّدٌ، ككَيِّسٍ: يَحيدُ عن ظِلِّهِ نَشاطاً، ولم يُوصَفْ مُذَكَّرٌ على فَعَلَى غيرُهُ. وسَمَّوْا: حَيْدَةَ وحِيداً، بالكسر، وأحْيَدَ وحَيادَةَ وحَيْدَانَ.</span><br><span>وحَيْدُ عُوَّرٍ، أو قُوَّرٍ، أو حُوَّرٍ: جَبَلٌ باليَمن فيه كَهْفٌ يُتَعَلَّمُ فيه السِّحْرُ.</span><br><span>وحايَدَهُ مُحايَدَةً وحِياداً: جانَبَه.</span><br><span>وما تَرَك حَياداً، كسَحابٍ: شيئاً، أو شَخْباً من اللَّبَنِ.</span><br><span>والحَيْدَةُ: نَظَرُ سَوْءٍ، وأرضٌ.</span><br><span>وحيدي حَيادِ، كَفيحِي فَياحِ.</span><br><span>وقَدَّ السَّيْرَ فَحيَّدهُ: جَعَلَ فيه حُيوداً.</span>"}]}}